# Z-STATE: Permeable by design — the boundary between yin and yang is the S-curve, which is simultaneously cut and bridge. The system can never seal because each pole carries the seed of its opposite. Z-Closure Risk: σ-collapse — if the distinction between poles is mistaken for hierarchy, the symbol degrades from generative paradox to dualistic moralism and the cycle freezes.
